22:18.817 --> 22:20.764
â™ª Drifts through the sky â™ª

22:20.788 --> 22:24.567
â™ª Mama's gonna sing you â™ª

22:24.591 --> 22:27.204
â™ª A lullaby. â™ª

22:27.995 --> 22:29.873
Okay, sweet pea,
it's time to go night-night.

22:29.897 --> 22:32.742
No, I'll sing to you
again tomorrow night.

22:32.766 --> 22:34.211
I love you.

22:37.304 --> 22:38.581
You mock, you die.

22:38.605 --> 22:42.585
No, no, no, not me. I am mock-less.

22:42.609 --> 22:44.889
Mauricio had a bad dream.

22:45.979 --> 22:48.425
Doesn't really understand
his mom being so far away.

22:48.449 --> 22:51.027
You and your ex must be pretty amicable

22:51.051 --> 22:52.896
for him to reach out to you like that.

22:52.920 --> 22:54.864
Mm, I wouldn't go straight to amicable,

22:54.888 --> 22:58.444
but we do both really love
our little boy.

23:01.728 --> 23:03.740
And I've never once worried

23:03.764 --> 23:05.618
that Mauricio's unsafe with him.

23:06.533 --> 23:08.334
Or that I might get shot in the back.

23:11.205 --> 23:12.916
The thought that that killer

23:12.940 --> 23:14.350
might get custody
of those little girls...

23:14.374 --> 23:16.045
I know.

23:16.710 --> 23:18.822
I take it you didn't find
any dirt on Derek?

23:18.846 --> 23:21.958
No, and I know Bull's got it in his head

23:21.982 --> 23:23.526
that there's something to find,

23:23.550 --> 23:25.084
but I'm coming up empty.

23:26.820 --> 23:28.865
Hey. What're you doing?

23:28.889 --> 23:30.133
Finish your food.

23:30.157 --> 23:32.686
No, no, I got to see this through.

23:33.160 --> 23:35.271
Amanda's social media feeds.

23:35.295 --> 23:37.941
I keep hoping I'll find
a picture of Amanda

23:37.965 --> 23:41.336
or one of the girls
with a bruise or a cast.

23:41.360 --> 23:44.547
Ah, what a wonderful thing to wish for.

23:44.571 --> 23:47.217
Now, Mr. Reed,

23:47.241 --> 23:49.152
did you and your wife ever fight?

23:50.245 --> 23:51.956
All couples fight,

23:52.880 --> 23:55.158
and we had our fair share.

23:55.626 --> 23:58.828
And then, when Amanda came and
told me she wanted a divorce,

23:58.852 --> 24:01.131
maybe we had more than our fair share,

24:02.689 --> 24:06.636
but we did our best not to
let it affect the children,

24:06.660 --> 24:09.067
not to let it upset Lila and Mae.

24:09.091 --> 24:13.710
Now we have heard stories
about your drinking.

24:13.734 --> 24:15.145
It's true.

24:16.136 --> 24:18.983
I let my drinking get
out of control for a while,

24:20.641 --> 24:23.086
and, uh, I know it's-it's no excuse,

24:23.110 --> 24:25.522
but I-I'd just lost both my parents,

24:25.546 --> 24:28.224
and I was trying to run a ranch,
and on top of that,

24:28.248 --> 24:30.790
my marriage was falling apart,

24:30.814 --> 24:32.170
so I drank.

24:32.194 --> 24:33.997
They're feeling sorry
for him, aren't they?

24:34.021 --> 24:35.732
I'm afraid so.

24:35.756 --> 24:37.668
I've not had a drink since...

24:39.545 --> 24:41.738
since the night of the accident.

24:44.131 --> 24:47.052
That was quite a performance
our sharpshooter dad gave.

24:47.701 --> 24:49.879
Any ideas about what
to come back at him with?

24:50.679 --> 24:52.849
Wait a minute.
Looks like we have company.

24:53.183 --> 24:55.185
Found you guys.

24:55.209 --> 24:56.753
I hope that's not all you found.

24:56.777 --> 24:58.555
Any luck with the photos?

24:58.579 --> 25:02.225
Actually, interestingly, I found
a peculiar absence of photos.

25:02.776 --> 25:04.427
You lost me at "actually."

25:04.451 --> 25:07.430
Turns out Amanda and Derek
went to Italy last year.

25:07.454 --> 25:09.732
Soon as she got there,
she started posting photos,

25:09.756 --> 25:12.502
but by day two of the trip, nothing.

25:12.526 --> 25:14.637
Wait a minute, they went on vacation?

25:14.661 --> 25:17.807
Who only posts a day's worth of
photos when they're on vacation?

25:17.831 --> 25:21.578
Nobody, certainly not
a obsessive poster like Amanda,

25:21.602 --> 25:23.947
so I worked every
Italian contact I ever had

25:23.971 --> 25:26.425
from my Homeland days, and...

25:27.140 --> 25:29.215
well, you can read for yourselves.

25:30.345 --> 25:31.454
<i>Mr. Reed,</i>

25:31.478 --> 25:32.822
it is our understanding

25:32.846 --> 25:34.057
that you and your late wife

25:34.081 --> 25:35.548
took a big trip to Italy last year.

25:37.117 --> 25:39.229
Objection, Your Honor. Relevance?

25:39.253 --> 25:42.098
Mr. Powers, you just spent
the entire morning questioning

25:42.122 --> 25:44.133
Mr. Reed about events in his marriage.

25:44.157 --> 25:46.903
Why shouldn't I allow opposing
counsel the same liberty?

25:46.927 --> 25:48.061
Overruled.

25:48.614 --> 25:50.340
Witness will answer the question.

25:51.241 --> 25:54.328
Yes. We did go to Italy.

25:54.768 --> 25:56.079
Amanda had always wanted to go,

25:56.103 --> 25:57.814
so I surprised her

25:57.838 --> 25:59.916
- with tickets for her birthday.
- Aw.

25:59.940 --> 26:01.284
That's nice.

26:01.308 --> 26:03.052
And while you were in Rome,

26:03.076 --> 26:04.954
Amanda ended up at the hospital

26:04.978 --> 26:07.323
with a broken cheekbone, is that correct?

26:07.347 --> 26:11.861
She did. We were staying
at this beautiful old hotel...

26:11.885 --> 26:15.698
very quaint... um, but the
bathtub was super slippery,

26:15.722 --> 26:17.533
and there was nothing to hold on to,

26:17.557 --> 26:19.035
nothing to give your feet traction

26:19.059 --> 26:20.903
when you were getting in or out.

26:20.927 --> 26:23.139
So sure enough, one night,

26:23.163 --> 26:25.942
Amanda fell and-and she cracked her cheek

26:25.966 --> 26:27.443
on the edge of the tub.

26:28.362 --> 26:30.813
No, I know, I know, that-that's what you

26:30.837 --> 26:33.483
told the hospital, but according
to hospital records,

26:33.507 --> 26:36.552
when Amanda had a moment alone,
she confessed that the injuries

26:36.576 --> 26:37.954
were a result of you hitting her.

26:37.978 --> 26:39.151
Objection.

26:39.175 --> 26:40.278
Your Honor,

26:40.302 --> 26:42.797
these records have not been
introduced or authenticated.

26:42.821 --> 26:44.663
Right you are. My mistake.

26:44.687 --> 26:47.730
Your Honor, I'd like
to introduce as Exhibit 27

26:47.754 --> 26:49.999
these hospital records

26:50.023 --> 26:54.070
and a notarized affidavit
from the hospital administrator.

26:54.346 --> 26:55.961
So admitted.

26:59.099 --> 27:02.054
So, exactly how hard
did you have to hit your wife

27:02.078 --> 27:04.347
to break her cheekbone, Mr. Reed?

27:04.371 --> 27:06.716
Must have been quite a wallop.

27:06.740 --> 27:08.323
Your Honor.

27:08.347 --> 27:10.353
Never mind. I withdraw the question.

27:10.863 --> 27:12.555
He's very good at this.

27:12.579 --> 27:14.057
â™ª Ow!

27:26.860 --> 27:28.463
Well...

27:28.929 --> 27:31.207
don't you look like the
cat who ate the canary.

27:31.231 --> 27:32.942
Actually, I haven't eaten yet.

27:32.966 --> 27:35.078
Which is why I ordered room service.

27:35.596 --> 27:37.639
You could hide in the bathroom
when they knock.

27:38.805 --> 27:40.305
You got my text?

27:40.329 --> 27:42.051
"The worm turns."

27:42.075 --> 27:45.188
- You the worm?
- Worm. Pig. Whatever works.

27:45.564 --> 27:47.390
We had a very good day in court today.

27:47.414 --> 27:49.225
Thought you'd want to hear about it.

27:49.735 --> 27:52.028
I gathered as much.

27:52.487 --> 27:54.698
Looks like you're doing just
what I thought you would do.

27:55.489 --> 27:56.956
You're kicking his ass.

27:58.994 --> 28:01.327
I'm sorry I called you a pig.

28:05.876 --> 28:07.533
I'm sorry I said
I want to sleep with you.

28:09.671 --> 28:11.147
Okay, that's a lie.

28:11.965 --> 28:13.216
That's okay.

28:13.240 --> 28:14.884
Mine was a lie, too.

28:14.908 --> 28:17.220
Hmm. Have you eaten?

28:17.244 --> 28:18.821
Mm-mm.

28:18.845 --> 28:20.089
Prove it.

28:20.515 --> 28:22.181
Bring that mouth over here.

28:28.023 --> 28:29.599
You should get that.

28:30.025 --> 28:31.734
It could be Benny about the case.

28:31.758 --> 28:33.569
It's a text.

28:33.593 --> 28:35.471
It'll hold. Benny's a big boy.

28:35.495 --> 28:37.646
He can hold down the fort all by himself.

28:37.670 --> 28:38.775
Hmm.

28:42.955 --> 28:45.104
I don't have a Benny.

28:52.212 --> 28:54.190
Oh. Wonder what this is about.

28:54.214 --> 28:56.492
I've been summoned
to the judge's chambers

28:56.516 --> 28:58.595
at 8:00 a.m. tomorrow morning.

28:59.513 --> 29:01.531
Well, how weird is this?

29:01.555 --> 29:04.066
<i>I</i> got summoned to the judge's chambers

29:04.090 --> 29:05.811
at 8:00 a.m. tomorrow morning.

29:06.760 --> 29:08.604
I just lost my appetite.

29:08.814 --> 29:10.273
Me, too.

29:13.519 --> 29:15.751
Mr. Powers, I gather
that your client believes

29:15.776 --> 29:18.148
the integrity of this trial
has been compromised?

29:18.173 --> 29:19.690
Yes, Your Honor.

29:19.690 --> 29:21.801
Mr. Reed has concerns
that one of my partners,

29:21.825 --> 29:23.169
Ms. Diana Lindsay,

29:23.193 --> 29:25.305
who represented him
in his criminal trial,

29:25.329 --> 29:28.541
divulged privileged information
to the petitioners' legal team.

29:28.565 --> 29:31.377
Your Honor, that is absolutely not true.

29:32.170 --> 29:35.114
Mr. Reed, this is a serious accusation.

29:35.138 --> 29:36.983
Do you have any evidence to back it up?

29:37.007 --> 29:40.622
I do. While we were preparing
for the last trial,

29:40.646 --> 29:43.890
I told Ms. Lindsay about what
happened to Amanda in Rome.

29:43.914 --> 29:46.059
I figured it could be misconstrued

29:46.083 --> 29:49.462
if it was brought up in court,
and I wanted her to be prepared.

29:50.105 --> 29:51.248
But the D.A.

29:51.272 --> 29:53.600
never mentioned it. Apparently
he never even heard about it.

29:53.624 --> 29:54.901
But out of nowhere,

29:54.925 --> 29:56.589
these folks from New York show up,

29:56.613 --> 29:58.438
and they know all about it.

29:58.822 --> 30:01.040
So I did some research.

30:01.064 --> 30:03.810
Turns out that Ms. Lindsay

30:03.834 --> 30:06.679
and Dr. Bull have worked
together in the past.

30:06.788 --> 30:08.437
Is this true, Ms. Lindsay?

30:10.541 --> 30:14.754
I do know Dr. Bull
professionally and socially.

30:15.630 --> 30:17.323
But I swear to you,

30:17.347 --> 30:20.860
I would never and I have never divulged

30:20.884 --> 30:23.329
confidential information about Mr. Reed

30:23.353 --> 30:25.031
or any other client to him.

30:25.055 --> 30:26.332
Or Mr. ColÃ³n.

30:26.808 --> 30:28.411
Or anyone else.

30:28.435 --> 30:30.069
I can assure you, Your Honor,

30:30.093 --> 30:33.139
my team discovered the incident
in Rome independently.

30:33.163 --> 30:35.675
And I'm happy to have my employee,

30:35.699 --> 30:37.744
who is a former Homeland Security agent,

30:37.768 --> 30:41.014
provide you with all
the documentation of her search.

30:41.038 --> 30:43.483
Well, I may circle back
and take you up on that offer.

30:43.507 --> 30:46.252
But let me ask you a question, Dr. Bull.

30:46.276 --> 30:50.657
How was it you came to represent
the Harpers in the first place?

30:50.681 --> 30:53.001
We're an awful long way
from New York City.

30:54.419 --> 30:55.962
Actually, I received a call

30:55.986 --> 30:57.363
from an attorney here in Houston.

30:57.387 --> 30:58.588
I asked him to.

30:59.772 --> 31:01.134
You asked him to?

31:01.158 --> 31:04.203
I did, Mr. Powers.

31:04.596 --> 31:05.939
I'm so sorry.

31:06.348 --> 31:07.740
As I'm sure you're aware,

31:07.764 --> 31:09.475
Ms. Lindsay,
this is a very serious violation

31:09.499 --> 31:12.045
of your duty of loyalty to your client.

31:12.069 --> 31:14.681
Now how am I supposed to believe
that you haven't also violated

31:14.705 --> 31:17.016
your duty of confidentiality, as well?

31:17.040 --> 31:19.519
I'm afraid I have no choice
but to refer this matter

31:19.543 --> 31:22.188
to the state bar for disciplinary action.

31:22.212 --> 31:23.423
You understand that?

31:23.447 --> 31:25.391
You may very well be facing suspension,

31:25.415 --> 31:26.849
even disbarment.

31:29.663 --> 31:30.928
I understand.

31:30.952 --> 31:33.333
Your Honor, on behalf
of myself and my colleagues

31:33.357 --> 31:35.786
at my firm, I want to apologize

31:35.810 --> 31:38.538
for this astounding breach of ethics.

31:38.562 --> 31:41.608
And I also want to move for a mistrial.

31:41.632 --> 31:44.277
The jury heard about
that incident in Rome.

31:44.301 --> 31:45.509
You can instruct them to disregard,

31:45.533 --> 31:47.847
but the damage is done.

31:47.871 --> 31:50.336
Actually, Your Honor,
I'm gonna save you the trouble.

31:51.559 --> 31:54.092
Given this turn of events,
I feel that I have no choice

31:54.116 --> 31:56.456
but to discharge my current attorney.

31:56.480 --> 31:59.125
And I think that you will agree
that it's not really fair that

31:59.149 --> 32:01.527
I should have to go out and find
new representation mid-trial.

32:01.551 --> 32:02.680
Your Honor,

32:02.704 --> 32:05.402
any calls for mistrial
is completely unwarranted.

32:05.426 --> 32:06.966
Closing arguments begin tomorrow.

32:06.990 --> 32:08.601
I don't want to hear it, Mr. ColÃ³n.

32:08.625 --> 32:10.570
I am granting the mistrial.

32:10.594 --> 32:13.272
And just to be clear,
if there is another trial,

32:13.296 --> 32:16.309
I will not allow any evidence
concerning the incident in Rome.

32:16.333 --> 32:19.879
<i>I asked you</i> point-blank why you were here

32:19.903 --> 32:23.149
and you never once mentioned
that woman's name.

32:23.173 --> 32:25.151
The woman who defended

32:25.175 --> 32:26.986
the man who killed our daughter,

32:27.010 --> 32:29.122
the woman who convinced a
jury to find him innocent.

32:29.146 --> 32:30.990
She had the best of intentions.

32:31.014 --> 32:33.026
We all had the best of intentions.

32:33.050 --> 32:34.827
Mr. ColÃ³n is at the courthouse right now

32:34.851 --> 32:36.162
filing for a new trial.

32:36.186 --> 32:38.531
Well, you call him right now
and you tell him to stop.

32:38.555 --> 32:40.631
You and your company
no longer represent us

32:40.655 --> 32:42.001
or the girls.

32:42.025 --> 32:44.170
I am bringing in an attorney from Dallas,

32:44.194 --> 32:46.439
see if there's any way to
salvage this thing at all.

32:46.463 --> 32:47.782
Mr. and Mrs. Harper...

32:47.806 --> 32:49.942
These came just before you arrived.

32:49.966 --> 32:51.811
It says we have to surrender the girls

32:51.835 --> 32:54.103
to Derek in less than 24 hours.

32:54.127 --> 32:57.016
Listen, I know we have failed
you, I know I failed you

32:57.040 --> 32:58.518
and I know you want to make a change,

32:58.542 --> 32:59.786
but please, let me get into this.

32:59.810 --> 33:01.087
Let me talk to the judge.

33:01.111 --> 33:02.410
Let me see what I can do.

33:02.434 --> 33:04.590
I've already seen what you can do,

33:04.614 --> 33:06.048
and you've done enough.

33:17.854 --> 33:19.505
You watching a movie?

33:19.529 --> 33:21.007
Can I show you something?

33:21.031 --> 33:23.576
Didn't you get the bulletin?

33:24.152 --> 33:25.578
Case is over.

33:25.602 --> 33:27.847
The children are going back to their dad,

33:27.871 --> 33:29.315
Victor and Sandy are getting a divorce,

33:29.339 --> 33:31.584
the forecast calls for 40 days
and 40 nights of rain.

33:31.608 --> 33:33.586
I'm trying to keep
a good attitude, but...

33:33.610 --> 33:35.421
What am I about to look at here?

33:35.445 --> 33:37.323
Remember way back when we
were trying to discredit

33:37.347 --> 33:38.791
Derek's story that he didn't know

33:38.815 --> 33:40.727
- Amanda was coming over that night?
- Mm-hmm.

33:40.751 --> 33:42.328
I went and got security footage

33:42.352 --> 33:44.333
from the grocery store
where she got his call.

33:44.357 --> 33:45.410
Okay.

33:45.435 --> 33:46.792
I don't know what I was hoping to find.

33:46.816 --> 33:48.701
Footage of a woman taking a phone call?

33:49.010 --> 33:50.559
But then I found it.

33:55.365 --> 33:56.843
I don't hear anything.

33:56.867 --> 33:58.211
That's because there's no sound.

33:58.235 --> 34:00.680
It's security footage. You don't
need sound to nab shoplifters.

34:00.704 --> 34:03.816
Okay. I'm lost.

34:03.840 --> 34:05.752
I don't understand
the purpose of this exercise.

34:05.776 --> 34:07.520
I was in the middle
of a perfectly good funk.

34:07.544 --> 34:08.878
Nothing suicidal, but still,

34:08.902 --> 34:10.389
dark, tiptoeing toward some form

34:10.413 --> 34:11.690
of self-destruction
and you interrupted me.

34:11.715 --> 34:13.192
Back when I worked at Homeland,

34:13.216 --> 34:16.362
I spent a lot of time looking
at CCTV footage without audio.

34:16.386 --> 34:18.420
And I got really good at lipreading.

34:18.444 --> 34:19.753
So when I saw this...

34:21.056 --> 34:25.371
...I enhanced the video
and, okay, look at her.

34:25.797 --> 34:28.074
She looks worried. I think she's saying,

34:28.098 --> 34:30.576
"Calm down, Honey Bear,
it'll be all right.

34:30.600 --> 34:32.637
I'll be there as soon as I can."

34:36.516 --> 34:39.351
Who calls their ex
they're in a custody battle with

34:39.376 --> 34:41.053
- "Honey Bear"?
- Exactly.

34:41.077 --> 34:44.422
I don't think Derek called
Amanda, I think Lila did.

34:44.447 --> 34:46.025
Which makes me wonder,

34:46.443 --> 34:48.353
if Lila was so upset

34:48.378 --> 34:50.996
that her mom felt she had
to rush to her side,

34:51.021 --> 34:54.960
do we honestly feel that she
would be asleep 15 minutes later

34:54.985 --> 34:56.435
after Amanda showed up?

34:56.458 --> 34:58.204
I need to talk to that little girl.

35:00.619 --> 35:03.942
Lila, you've seen me
around here, haven't you?

35:04.962 --> 35:06.360
I'm a friend of your grandparents.

35:07.964 --> 35:11.372
You know, a lot of people
are trying to figure out

35:11.885 --> 35:14.275
where you and your sister should live,

35:14.299 --> 35:15.717
and I would like to know what you think.

35:16.781 --> 35:18.405
Hmm? I know, it's,

35:19.601 --> 35:22.395
it's hard to say what you want sometimes.

35:23.855 --> 35:25.815
Maybe you don't want
to hurt anyone's feelings?

35:38.216 --> 35:39.750
Maybe you're scared?

35:41.998 --> 35:43.797
Does this guy have a name?

35:44.626 --> 35:45.694
Tuxedo.

35:45.718 --> 35:47.629
Oh...

35:48.296 --> 35:50.465
Tuxedo.

35:51.023 --> 35:52.342
Excellent.

35:53.932 --> 35:55.199
You know what people call me?

35:56.805 --> 35:58.431
Bull.

35:58.998 --> 36:01.384
It's my name.
Well, it's kind of a nickname,

36:01.408 --> 36:04.279
because my first name
is actually "Jason."

36:04.303 --> 36:06.615
- Bull.
- Bull.

36:06.639 --> 36:09.117
I know. It's funny.

36:09.692 --> 36:11.687
Your mom had a nickname
for you, didn't she?

36:12.445 --> 36:13.660
Was it...

36:13.684 --> 36:15.090
"Honey Bear"?

36:15.865 --> 36:17.326
Mm.

36:17.951 --> 36:20.085
You loved your mom a lot, didn't you?

36:22.688 --> 36:24.733
You remember the other day,
you got upset,

36:24.757 --> 36:27.919
when your grandma was
yelling at your grandpa?

36:29.254 --> 36:31.130
I think I might know why.

36:32.549 --> 36:35.177
You were scared, weren't you?

36:35.201 --> 36:37.679
Married people, yelling at each other?

36:38.179 --> 36:40.105
It's scary, isn't it?

36:43.226 --> 36:45.228
The last time you saw your mom,

36:47.063 --> 36:50.782
she was yelling at your dad, wasn't she?

36:55.046 --> 36:56.981
Daddy shot Mommy.

37:02.782 --> 37:04.789
You saw it, didn't you?

37:10.253 --> 37:11.947
It's all my fault.

37:11.971 --> 37:13.448
I am the reason she came over.

37:13.472 --> 37:14.916
I called her.

37:15.466 --> 37:18.320
Oh, no, no, no. Lila,

37:19.345 --> 37:21.423
it's what mommies are supposed to do.

37:22.181 --> 37:24.893
They come when we need them.

37:25.268 --> 37:26.769
They were yelling,

37:27.770 --> 37:30.565
and then she came upstairs to get us

37:30.589 --> 37:32.525
and he shot her in the back.

37:33.776 --> 37:37.539
He said if I told, I'd never
see my sister ever again.

37:38.114 --> 37:40.542
Okay. Come here.

37:40.566 --> 37:42.619
It's okay.

37:43.569 --> 37:45.213
It's gonna be okay.

37:48.541 --> 37:51.453
Dr. Bull, Mr. ColÃ³n.

37:51.477 --> 37:52.781
I thought my order was quite clear:

37:52.805 --> 37:55.957
the girls were to be returned
to their father's custody <i>today.</i>

37:57.008 --> 37:58.794
Turns out there <i>is</i> a problem, Your Honor.

37:58.818 --> 38:00.395
We have it on good authority

38:00.419 --> 38:03.770
that Mr. Reed is going to be unavailable

38:03.794 --> 38:06.068
to take care of the children
in the near future.

38:06.092 --> 38:07.969
What are you talking about?
That's preposterous.

38:07.993 --> 38:10.072
We had a little chat with
the D.A. this morning,

38:10.096 --> 38:12.446
and he was very interested to hear

38:12.470 --> 38:14.943
that there was a witness
to your wife's murder...

38:15.301 --> 38:17.746
your daughter...
and that you threatened her

38:17.770 --> 38:20.972
so that she would not say what she saw.

38:23.117 --> 38:24.586
Fine.

38:24.610 --> 38:28.323
You can talk to the district
attorney all you want.

38:28.623 --> 38:30.659
Double jeopardy still applies.

38:30.683 --> 38:32.961
I can't be retried for Amanda's death.

38:32.985 --> 38:35.197
Ah, you're right...
you can't be tried again

38:35.221 --> 38:36.898
for your wife's murder.

38:36.922 --> 38:39.434
But you can be tried
for witness tampering.

38:39.458 --> 38:40.825
Gentlemen!

38:42.679 --> 38:45.615
Fun fact: In Texas, if you
tamper with a murder trial,

38:45.639 --> 38:47.987
you get the same punishment
you would have gotten

38:48.011 --> 38:49.144
if you were convicted

38:49.168 --> 38:51.146
of the murder itself. Remind me, Benny,

38:51.170 --> 38:52.514
what is the punishment again?

38:52.538 --> 38:53.982
Life in prison.

38:55.007 --> 38:57.777
Derek Reed, you're under arrest
for witness tampering.

39:01.406 --> 39:03.291
You have the right to remain silent...

39:03.315 --> 39:05.026
Well...

39:05.050 --> 39:07.963
I could've done without the theatrics.

39:07.987 --> 39:10.365
- Eh.
- And I certainly can't condone

39:10.389 --> 39:12.367
how you came to be involved in the case,

39:12.391 --> 39:15.081
but I do believe
that you did what you did

39:15.105 --> 39:16.972
in the best interest of the children.

39:16.996 --> 39:19.063
- Thank you, Your Honor.
- Thank you.

39:21.934 --> 39:24.576
You know, Judge, there is someone else

39:24.600 --> 39:28.339
who did what she did... in the
best interests of the children.

39:40.764 --> 39:42.453
I checked out yesterday.

39:45.283 --> 39:46.835
You got my text.

39:46.859 --> 39:48.837
"The worm turned again.

39:48.861 --> 39:50.839
"This time I stepped on him.

39:50.863 --> 39:52.941
"Then I dragged my shoe
along the sidewalk

39:52.965 --> 39:55.944
"till there was nothing left
of him but a dark smear

39:55.968 --> 39:57.579
- on the concrete."
- Hmm.

39:57.603 --> 39:59.414
You're quite the poet.

39:59.438 --> 40:01.650
- Well, it's a gift.
- Mm.

40:02.091 --> 40:03.652
Girls are with their grandparents

40:03.676 --> 40:05.810
and seem... very happy.

40:07.138 --> 40:08.514
Thank you.

40:09.432 --> 40:11.059
Sorry you lost your job.

40:11.434 --> 40:12.928
Well, sometimes you got to choose

40:12.952 --> 40:15.354
between being a good lawyer
or being a good person.

40:15.955 --> 40:17.599
I'll get a new job.

40:17.623 --> 40:20.168
Heck, I might just start my own firm,

40:20.192 --> 40:22.704
if I don't get disbarred first.

40:23.237 --> 40:24.773
That's not gonna happen.

40:24.797 --> 40:25.864
How do you know?

40:28.242 --> 40:29.444
What did you do?

40:30.203 --> 40:32.914
I told the judge that I was
in the doghouse with you,

40:32.938 --> 40:34.382
and it would go a long way

40:34.406 --> 40:37.552
if maybe he could not
press "send" on that e-mail.

40:37.576 --> 40:39.855
And then I appealed
to his sense of fair play,

40:39.879 --> 40:41.857
and then I told him
I'd be thrilled to have his son

40:41.881 --> 40:44.359
do an internship at TAC next year.

40:44.717 --> 40:47.028
That may not have been
the exact order of events.

40:47.804 --> 40:49.096
What are you doing this weekend?

40:50.756 --> 40:54.269
I've heard that line somewhere before.

40:55.853 --> 40:56.938
What's this?

40:56.962 --> 40:58.815
Plane tickets to New York City.

40:59.357 --> 41:00.709
Seat next to mine.

41:00.733 --> 41:03.334
We leave in three and a half hours.

41:04.796 --> 41:06.864
That is, if you want to come.

41:09.775 --> 41:11.077
Please...

41:12.011 --> 41:13.999
just... come.

41:16.998 --> 41:18.994
Think you could get me one
of those internships at TAC?

41:19.489 --> 41:20.833
Well...

41:20.858 --> 41:22.297
I'll put in a good word.

41:22.321 --> 41:23.598
Hmm.

41:23.622 --> 41:26.368
So, a spontaneous weekend
in New York City.

41:26.392 --> 41:28.737
- Mm.
- Sounds great.

41:29.053 --> 41:31.006
What hotel you put me in?

41:31.030 --> 41:32.607
Hotel.

41:32.631 --> 41:34.609
I knew there was something I forgot.

